    Professional Summary

    Click to edit text

    Section colors
    Duplicate section
    Delete section

    Sean Altenburg is an accomplished professional drummer with over two decades of performance experience spanning multiple genres including rock, Christian contemporary, and '90s alternative music. Based in the Toledo, Ohio area, Sean has established himself as a versatile and reliable performer with an extensive touring and recording background.

     Performance Experience & Notable Collaborations

    Click to edit text

    Section colors
    Duplicate section
    Delete section

    Sean's professional career includes significant touring and recording experience with multiple bands:


    Skittle Bots (2015-present) - All '90s cover band serving the Toledo metropolitan area


    Southbound Fearing (2006-2010) - Extended touring and recording commitment


    The Perfect Addiction (2005-2006) - Professional recording and performance

    Spikefoot Tragedy (2001-2004) - Recording and touring with this Christian rock band

    Musical Background & Training

    Click to edit text

    Section colors
    Duplicate section
    Delete section

    Sean's musical journey began in early childhood and has been characterized by consistent growth and achievement:


    Early Development: Self-taught foundation beginning with household percussion

    Formal Training: Private drum instruction combined with comprehensive school band participation

    Academic Excellence: Competed at the highest levels in solo and ensemble competitions throughout high school

    Diverse Experience: Extensive background in marching band, concert band, and jazz ensemble performance

    Ministry Experience: Active worship team member and Christian music ministry participant
